# Translation & billing tier scope (InterpreterAI)

## Final Boss 3 (canonical product snapshot)

Single named baseline for **transcription** (browser → Soniox, identical for all plans) and **translation engine** (server `POST /translate`):

| Segment | DB `plan_type` examples | Translation engine |
|--------|-------------------------|---------------------|
| **Default signup** | `trial-libre` | LibreTranslate (machine) |
| **Basic / Professional** (paid) | `basic-libre`, `professional-libre` (PayPal sets these on activate); legacy `basic`, `professional`, `basic-openai`, `professional-openai` also route to Libre | LibreTranslate |
| **Platinum / Unlimited** | `platinum`, `unlimited`; admin label `platinum-libre` uses **OpenAI** like platinum | OpenAI (`gpt-4o-mini` stack) |
| **Legacy OpenAI trials** (admin only / old accounts) | `trial`, `trial-openai` | OpenAI |

- **PayPal** `subscription_plan` stays `basic` | `professional` | `platinum` for billing; **`plan_type`** after activation is `basic-libre` / `professional-libre` / `platinum`. Subscription cancel → `trial-libre` + inactive.
- **Engine switch** is server-only (`planUsesMachineTranslationStack` in `usage.ts` → `useMachineTranslation` in `transcription.ts`). Client dispatch is unchanged.
- **Git:** tag **`final-boss-3`** marks this baseline (move tag on intentional freezes).

## Do not change without explicit approval

- **OpenAI path** in `transcription.ts`: prompts, retries, cost accounting, and behavior for plans that use `callOpenAI` (Platinum, Unlimited, legacy `trial` / `trial-openai`, etc.).
- **Client** `use-transcription.ts`: no plan-specific branches — same STT + translate dispatch for every tier.

## Allowed to change (Libre / machine path only)

- **`planUsesMachineTranslationStack` is true** for that user: `basic-pro-translate.ts`, `libretranslate.ts`, Libre-only glossary/masking shortcuts in `transcription.ts`, and **`effectivePlanTypeForTranslation`** when preserving PayPal lag semantics for `trial-libre` upgrades.
- After completing requested work, **commit and push** to `main` unless the user says not to.
